Tony,
       I think the odds are you would win your bet.  Some ~20 years ago I had a 
Dodgy van in which the PO had installed a pop-up hatch, maybe 12" square, on 
the roof toward the rear of the van.  When I would open this hatch, I would get 
a distinct smell of exhaust at speed.  Never checked it with a smoke bomb... I 
was convinced when I got dizzy after an hour's driving time.  On another van, 
the PO had installed Jalousie windows in the rear side locations.  Same result, 
only more so.

I still have an aftermarket sunroof, guessing 15" x 30", that I never got 
around to installing.  Maybe someday I will cut the roof and put it in; but you 
can bet your virtual bucks it will go up toward the front of the van.  

Friday content: if anyone is interested in the sunroof, the price would be 
verrrry reasonable.  Glenn

